******
[2] Transparency, dairy products recall
Date: Fri 28 Oct 2016
Source: RIA Federal Press [in Russian, machine trans. summarized, edited]
http://tinyurl.com/h6musxk


Vladimir Putin called on the head of the Ministry of Agriculture not to hide the problem of foot and mouth disease of dairy products.

"Alexander, you are working with good people, I do not doubt their qualifications, the only thing I want to ask you: There should be nothing to hide; you have to be transparent and clear, and our country, as well as our partners abroad, need to know and to have full information about what is happening and what is being done to arrest this threat," his words according to TASS.

Alexander Tkachev has promised to solve the problem.

Previously, Federal Press reported that major retailers have received a letter from Rospotrebnadzor requesting the removal from circulation of almost 4000 tons of dairy products.

[Byline: Alexander Balayev]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The major (almost 4000 tons) recall of distributed dairy products by a large producer which received milk from the affected farm, mainly from the markets of the capital Moscow, has caused confusion and, according to the media, even some panic among consumers beyond Moscow (e.g. today's [28 Oct 2016] media report at http://tinyurl.com/zgoln5g). This was related also to the published relevant production period, from 1-19 Oct 2016. Notably, the FMD outbreak in Vladimir was 1st reported on 20 Oct 2016.

On top of that, the Russian health establishment (both medics and vets) traditionally consider, in striking difference with views elsewhere, FMD as a (significant) zoonosis. Official Russian health and veterinary sources describe human FMD infections, mainly milk-borne, which, in some cases, would -- according to them -- require hospitalisation. This debatable opinion is to be addressed in more detail in one of our next postings.

The transparency, advised by V. Putin, will be served by the early publication of the genotyping results.

The intervention of Vladimir Putin rings some bells (March 2001, PM Tony Blair, FMD epizootic in the UK, https://www.theguardian.com/pictures/image/0,8543,-12104142447,00.html_?). - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4593046,98.]
